This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes an algorithm that incorporates feature extraction cost during training to minimize cpu-time during testing. It may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) as these fields heavily rely on machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper may fall under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as these fields also deal with optimization and efficiency.
